
[1]justness

   JUST'NESS, n. Accuracy; exactness; as the justness of proportions.

   1. Conformity to truth; as the justness of a description or
   representation.

   2. Justice; reasonableness; equity; as the justness of a cause or of a
   demand. [Justness is properly applied to things, and justice to
   persons; but the distinction is not always observed.]
